The paper proposes a novel deep learning architecture for indoor localization using fingerprint samples from smartphones. The approach involves using artificial neural networks, generative adversarial networks, and sparse coding. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), systems and control (cs.SY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
